ight'; font-size:11pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The four major high street banks operating in NI all are owned externally. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Local management</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> has limited discretion and is more likely to be involved in administering Group /Corporate policy set in Dublin, Copenhagen or London/Edinburgh. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Core policy making such as Group Credit Risk management/ IT infrastructure / capital allocation across busine</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ss units/ customer segmentation &amp; marketing</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">policies </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">are all in effect set outside NI</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Three of the four</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> high street banks </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">are subject to EC/EU State Aid restructuring programmes restricting </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">or constraining their freedom of action at </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">policy making</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> level</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Although Santander for example has a high street presence its NI business customers will have their accounts handled by business banking centres in Glasgow or Newport or London in exactly the same way as any other customer anywhere in the UK and su</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">bject to exactly the same terms &amp; conditions, charges eligibility &amp; lending criteria. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">6)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The major issue in NI banking is that, bar the Progressive Building Society, there are no locally headquartered </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">financial services business and therefore no local contro</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">l of policy.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">7)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The NI banking market has traditionally operated on the basis of cross-border / all-Ireland structures. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">8)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">This model is </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">now </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">effectively dead </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">largely</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> for reasons of politics &amp;</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> economic nationalism arising out of the need for EU/ECB funding to rescue both the Irish banks &amp; state. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">9)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This situation arose out of a failure of regulation leading Irish banks to over-extend themselves </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">both </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">domestically &amp; externally.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">10)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This mistake will no</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">t be repeated, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">political and public opinion will not tolerate </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">regulators in ROI</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> allowing the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> major </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">tax-payer rescued </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">‘pillar’ banks allocating scare capital to support business in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">outside the state</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">t the expense of business &amp; individuals within the state.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">11)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There will </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">also be political, business public &amp; social pressure on ROI banks to focus on their domestic market and support local economic growth and development. This is not a narrow political point. In the UK we see the mirror image of this in the withdr</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">awal of RBS/Lloyds for example from overseas markets and market segments nationally &amp; internationally.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">12)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We must also recognize the different political &amp; legislative trajectories within &amp; between the UK &amp; Ireland and specifically issues arising from </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">regulatory developments within the Eurozone sub-set of countries within the EU and the UK focus on re-negotiations/ opt-outs/ subsidiarity etc.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">13)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The practical consequences for NI are likely to be concentration</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> of banking in fewer players, l</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ess choice, less </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">competition and higher costs. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The possible break-up of RBS/Ulster Bank.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">14)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Resolution of this issue is not solely or even substantially in the hands of RBS management nor UK politicians - </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">something which seems almost entirely missing from much public debate! </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">15)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">You should note that the EC has recently allowed Bank of Ireland to retain an insurance operation in Republic of Ireland which it had previously decided should be disposed of as a cond</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ition of State Aid. The EC rationale for this was that there were no realistic buyers for the business in the market.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">16)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The quid pro quo is that BOI must shed its corporate &amp; business banking activities in GB either through run-down or by sale</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">although it i</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s able to</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">retain</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">those in NI.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The NI businesses are now exposed in that there will be loss of scope &amp; scale in service provision.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">17)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It should also be noted that the BoI is now focusing on serving </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">personal business only </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in GB through Post Office Financial </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Services (POFS)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">delivered through PO branches &amp; supported by centralised deposit &amp; lending administration and on-line banking</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">18)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The precedent has also been set &amp; the next revision of State Aid for BoI (&amp; there will almost inevitably be one) could require </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the disposal of its NI corporate &amp; business banking. This would leave the rump of its personal business which could be serviced via POFS. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">19)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The bank stake in POFS is a saleable asset in the last resort &amp; is now a hostage to fortune in that disposal may be m</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">andated by EC/EU. The possibility of BoI exiting NI is no longer unthinkable.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">20)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I cannot comment on the status of Allied Irish/First Trust businesses other than to note that there were apparently no buyers when the business was put on the market a number of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">years ago. Given that Allied Irish remains subject to EC/EU State Aids considerations then that business may also be vulnerable</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> regardless of public positions taken by management.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">21)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In this context the price of future State Aid approvals for RBS may well be </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">disposal of at least </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the Ulster Bank business in RoI regardless of the ‘good bank/bad bank’ arguments propounded by politicians/RBS executive management/board.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">22)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">EC rules cannot </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">however </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">prevent individual customers opting to remain with their </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">current bank regardless of whether or not ’their branch’ is sold. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">23)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The best forward-looking solution would seem to be to encourage the full absorption of the Ulster Bank NI business into RBS proper w</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">here it would benefit from the full resources of RBS unmediated by a ‘local’ headquarters.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">24)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Given the lack of buyers for more substantial branch networks being disposed of by</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> both</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Lloyds &amp; RBS disposal </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">of the Ulster Bank business in NI would not seem to be </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">a realistic option.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The position of the staff of the former Irish Bank Resolution Corporation</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">25)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I do not know enough about this issue to comment but difficult to see as a significant forward-looking issue</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">unfortunate as it may be for the individuals involved. Matters would seem to revolve around employment law &amp; the basis on which Anglo Irish/IBRC operated in the UK </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">4 Access to finance particularly for SME’s, </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">5 Lack of effectiveness of national </span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">initiatives to help aid economic recovery</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">6 Lack of availability of detailed regional lending data</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">26)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I regard these issues as being intimately linked. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">27)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">My recollection is that the NI banks were never more than ‘bit players’ in national ’trade’</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> bodies such as British Bankers Association/APACs etc.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">28)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Given their scope &amp; scale they would tend to be policy takers rather than makers.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">29)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For that reason I suspect that national initiatives would receive only ‘lip service’ - the minimum necessary &amp; no more.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Stats will show that use of for example SFLGS by NI banks was pathetic</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the preference being to focus on own in-house products rather than develop the processes &amp; practices &amp; staff training</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">necessary to support such initiatives, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">such lack of support </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">urn stifle</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> demand - a bit of a self-fulfilling prophecy in a sense!</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">30)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">My understanding is that much business lending remains in effect asset backed lending</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, security over assets first then looking at profitability &amp; repayment capacity</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">31)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For so long as there is a significant overhang of property, whether warehoused in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">NAMA or elsewhere, then property values will remain under pressure and represent a significant constraint on business lending. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">32)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In these circumstances access to national init</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">iatives based for example on partial Govt guarantees for otherwise unsecured </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&amp; cash-flow based </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">business lending will remain essential. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">33)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The overwhelming proportion of businesses</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in NI are in the micro to small category and more likely to benefit from or re</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">quire cash-flow based rather than asset backed lending. Past experience of SFLGS does not offer much comfort in this respect.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">34)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I think the point needs to be made that ‘SME’s’ are not a single market with common needs. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">35)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Many SME’s in the micro to small categ</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ory will be largely locally orientated with substantial demand for transaction handling services - cash/ cheques/card payments - which are expensive to provide and largely unprofitable for banks</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">36)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Any borrowing requirements</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">will be relatively small and only</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> marginally profitable once all admin &amp; overhead costs are considered </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">37)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Paradoxically many large businesses operating in NI will have similar profile - transaction-based needs for electronic payments of salaries &amp; wages, suppliers, &amp; receipt of payments wit</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">h minimum local overnight balances with borrowings /deposits</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">largely managed by corporate treasury &amp; held in GB based branches</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">38)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Businesses in the small to medium category are likely to have the more complex needs not just for transaction services but cash </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">flow lending (overdrafts) and capital investment (term loans/ equity/venture capital finance, trade related financing. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">39)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This should /could be a profitable mix for banks but unfortunately banks have spent the last 20 years or so paying extolling the virtues</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> of relationship banking whilst at the same time promoting financial promiscuity - by which I mean offering stand-alone products to non-current account holders</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">40)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Whilst this promiscuity does bring competition to the market it also fractures the ‘relationshi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">p’ model with no </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">bank having a clear overall picture of business needs hence driving the imperative for asset based lending and even then there may be differing views as to which lender has prior claim over which assets, all of which acts to constrain lend</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ing limits</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">41)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There is no excuse for excluding lending from the proposed post code reporting. How will direct banks with no physical presence in NI report their figures? </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">42)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">If Santander/Tesco/Sainsbury /M&amp;S/First Direct/ for example all report their UK </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">lending </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">by post code then the ’unclassified’ stuff could be considered NI by default (I know it won’t be that simple but deduction by exception is possible!) </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">43)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Regional lending data must be made available otherwise </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">public policy making </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">will occur in a partial vacuu</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">m and risks being uninformed. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">44)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Likewise banks themselves will be acting in a vacuum, making assumptions about the potential market for financial services which may not be realistic (there are both upsides &amp; downsides to this)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Access to banking in rural co</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">mmunities</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">45)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This is I am afraid essentially yesterday’s issue.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">46)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Branches have been closing for years &amp; the trend - visible across the UK &amp; Europe - will continue and indeed is accelerating. I believe that recent stats based on research </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">y a UK university confirm this but may not show that rural communities are being anymore affected by this than deprived urban communities.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">47)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It needs to be recognized that t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">he role of the branch has changed over the years, currently configured largely as ‘sa</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">les outlets’ even that function is becoming redundant with much marketing/sales /account servicing being done remotely by phone /on-line or social media. Salaries &amp; wages &amp; benefits have been paid electronically for decades</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. It is stated Govt policy to enc</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ourage payment into accounts – the basic bank account is an outrun of this. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Financial inclusion policy is about bank accounts for all not dependence on cash transactions.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">48)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">An increasing number of transactions are by card &amp; card technology is changing almost</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> by the day. No-one any more has a need to visit a branch</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">49)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Recent entrants to the NI personal financial services market - Tesco, Sainsbury &amp; M&amp; S for example- use their supermarket outlets as service points.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">50)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The example of the BOI /Post Office joint venture</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> is relevant here with cash transactions available through Post Offices/ATM‘s etc, not branches.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">51)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">All other services including accounting transaction processing, credit scoring for personal lending including mortgages, personal loans &amp; credit cards can be</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> centralised &amp; handled remotely.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">52)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Even business lending seems increasingly based on ’credit scoring’ principles.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">53)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It is strange to note however than in respect of investment advice ‘past performance is no guarantee of or guide to future performance’ whereas </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">behaviour based credit </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">scoring relies precisely on extrapolating past performance to predict future behaviour</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">54)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">‘Relationship banking’ no longer seems to require face to face contact being replaced by contact by phone/internet/social media channels - the tra</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ditional branch has no future and only a limited lifespan.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">55)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The issue should really be about adapting to new reality rather than preserving the past.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.25pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>